# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Evidence + reports — BLOCK-EVERYTHING policy (Session 54, post-audit)
#
# Previous policy listed individual extensions (.zip, .pdf, .png, …) and
# DELIBERATELY allowed text formats (.txt, .json, .csv, .tsv, .md) under
# the assumption they'd be sanitized. They weren't: the audit found
# 746 tracked files under docs/reports/evidence/ + reports/ containing
# raw OCR responses, I-821/I-765 form dumps, and the owner's real PII
# (name, address, DOB, A-number, SSN-pattern).
#
# New policy: ALL evidence content is sensitive by default. The folder
# may exist for local runs, but NOTHING under it ships in commits unless
# explicitly force-added with `git add -f` after manual sanitization
# review by the owner. Same rule for reports/ root.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# docs/reports/evidence/ — entire subtree blocked
docs/reports/evidence/
# (Keep the folder marker so future runs have a place to write to.)
!docs/reports/evidence/.gitkeep
!docs/reports/evidence/README.md

# reports/ root — booklet OCR runs, benchmark CSVs, owner test outputs
reports/booklet-stability-*/
reports/booklet-synthetic-*
reports/booklet-multi-sample-*
reports/BOOKLET_*.md
reports/*-response.json
reports/owner_*

# Real user documents — PII, never committed
qa-shots/private/
qa-shots/ua_passport_real.*
qa-shots/booklet_*
test-fixtures/owner/
docs/audit/REAL_DOC_GROUND_TRUTH.local.yaml

# Build artifacts
apps/web/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
apps/web/public/brand/archive/

# Real client/owner documents — PII, NEVER commit
test-fixtures/real-docs/

# Private QA data — PII / ground-truth / benchmark raw, NEVER commit
qa-private/
reports/
